    <detaileddescription>
<para>Type traits and methods to enable type safe bit field operators for an enum. usage: template&lt;&gt; struct EnableBitMaskOperators&lt; MyEnumType &gt; { static const bool ENABLE = true; }; after this one can set bitfields with | and |=, like MyEnumType value = FLAG1 | FLAG2; and test them with &amp;, like: if( myFlag &amp; FLAG2 ) // do something </para>
